node.text:
IT'S THE NPS-AVERSARY!
From the early days of "hey, maybe we should keep this place wild", through pivotal moments of the very fabric of modern American history, the NPS continues to protect and preserve the places that make us who we are. 
Today marks 103 years of National Parks Service – we think a toast is in order! Video by @maxeyfish #radparks #findyourpark

node.title: The (unofficial) History of the National Parks

node.text:
PRE-SALE: Coolers are back! This summer just got a little greener ♻️ We teamed up with @igloocoolers on these coolers—the first of its kind made from recycled post-consumer plastic. Now you just have to decide what to pack for lunch... #leaveitbetter #radparks #findyourpark

Please allow until 7/28 for our team to ship out orders.

node.text:
Did you know @glaciernps' famous Going-to-the-Sun Road connects the east and west sides of the park? This 50-mile drive crosses the Continental Divide at Logan Pass and is filled with awe-inspiring landscapes, glaciers, and cascading waterfalls 🤩 Interested? Be sure to grab a ticket during your visit!

Ticket information can be found on the Glacier National Park official website: https://www.nps.gov/glac/planyourvisit/gtsrticketedentry.htm

node.text:
Of course when we think of @sequoiakingsnps we think of towering trees, but there's so much more to discover on your visit! Backpacking allows visitors to further explore the park; With over 800 miles of maintained trails, hikers are able to fully immerse themselves in the 800,000+ acres of designated wilderness 🌲  Need some help planning your next trip? Check out our Park Finder!  #radparks #findyourpark #leaveitbetter
